	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Looks right especially with the Vcc match up from the other controllers and everything.  The ground is obvious just based on the cross-hashed area.
<br />
<br />Do you have a multimeter?  you could always double check that you've got 5v from Vcc and Gnd right before plugging something in.  If it doesn't work as you planned you could try swapping D- and D+ but don't swap anything else.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


